The paper proposes a new framework for decision theory that goes beyond classical utility maximisation, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of higher-order functions and operators suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on preferences and goals is also relevant to game theory (cs.GT) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the consideration of context and process suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SI).
